Arsenal have officially reached an agreement with two defenders, Pablo Mari and Cedric Soares to join the club on a permanent deal. Mari and Soares initially joined Arsenal on loan in the January transfer window but have impressed for the Gunners so far after winning the FA Cup trophy earlier this month. Arsenal stated this in a statement on its official website on Monday. The statement read: “We have reached an agreement with both Pablo Mari and Cedric Soares to join the club on permanent deals. “Both players joined us initially on loan in January, and after impressing on and off the pitch over the past eight months, all parties have agreed to make their moves permanent.” Pablo, 26, joined Mikel Arteta’s side from Brazilian side Flamengo. Cedric, 28, joined Arsenal from Southampton.